From: Mason Chang <mason-cw.chang@mediatek.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Sep 2025 11:12:08 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: mtk_eth_soc: change napi poll weight to 256

This parameter will strongly affect the peak throughput of the SW path.
Increasing the NAPI poll weight reduces per-interrupt overhead and
lowers latency variance under high packet rates.

[dpawlik: ported from mtk-openwrt-feeds 25.12 999-eth-17;
 adapted for 6.18 which has two netif_napi_add calls (no RSS/LRO)
 and uses eth->rx_napi instead of eth->rx_napi[0].napi]
Signed-off-by: Daniel Pawlik <pawlik.dan@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.c | 5 +++--
 drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.h | 1 +
 2 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.h
@@ -44,3 +44,4 @@
 #define MTK_FQ_DMA_HEAD		32
 #define MTK_FQ_DMA_LENGTH	2048
+#define MTK_NAPI_WEIGHT		256
 #define MTK_RX_ETH_HLEN		(ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN)
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.c
@@ -5774,3 +5774,5 @@
 	strcpy(eth->dummy_dev->name, "mtk_eth");
-	netif_napi_add(eth->dummy_dev, &eth->tx_napi, mtk_napi_tx);
-	netif_napi_add(eth->dummy_dev, &eth->rx_napi, mtk_napi_rx);
+	netif_napi_add_weight(eth->dummy_dev, &eth->tx_napi, mtk_napi_tx,
+			      MTK_NAPI_WEIGHT);
+	netif_napi_add_weight(eth->dummy_dev, &eth->rx_napi, mtk_napi_rx,
+			      MTK_NAPI_WEIGHT);
